c="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Soloing summoning mobs</span><hr size=1> People say that they can solo summoning mobs. I would like to know some of the tactics used to do this and which mob it is.<br>
<br>
The only summoning mobs I solo myself with any regularity are the deep cavern lotuses in Fungus Grove and even at lv 60 they can be quite a handfull. It is all a matter of allowing the pet to tank and taunt, while nuking enough to take it down before the pet dies.<br>
<br>
I don't have the epic pet, so that is not an option.<br>
 <p>nmee - commander of mudhills<br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=407265">nmee's magelo</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><br>
</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#989dca><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=krankenthegnome>Kranken the Gnome</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Arch Mage</span><br>  Posts: 403<br> <font color=#333333>(3/4/03 12:06:38 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=452.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Soloing summoning mobs</span><hr size=1> Depends on the mob. <br>
<br>
If your pet has high enough aggro you can often /pet hold when you're ready to chain in another pet, let the pet run away a bit and be summoned by the mob, then you're sure you won't be summoned when you chain in another.<br>
<br>
It's much easier epic/61 air though. With those pets you can just nuke/heal and it's less of a problem. <p>------------<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=433620">Kranken</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Convoker<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Xev<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->&quot;Where's my pet..?&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=skildpade>skildpade</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 233<br> <font color=#333333>(3/4/03 1:07:11 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=452.topic&index=2>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Soloing summoning mobs</span><hr size=1> Something like:<br>
<br>
Summoning has a timer, <br>
<br>
so backing off the pet to get it summoned will give you time to summon a new pet without getting summoned? <br>
<br>
and be carefull only to nuke at the end?<br>
 <p>nmee - commander of mudhills<br>
