<br>
And nuking with anything more then burst of flame is probably a bad idea, since otherwise when you chain in a new pet you'll have significant aggro and probably get summoned a few times before the pet taunts it off. <p>------------<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END--><!--EZCODE LINK START--><a href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=433620">Kranken</a><!--EZCODE LINK END--><!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Arch Convoker<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->Xev<!--EZCODE BR START--><br /><!--EZCODE BR END-->&quot;Where's my pet..?&quot;</p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#dcdeed><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub102.ezboard.com/bthemagicianstower.showUserPublicProfile?gid=scrubfire>scrubfire</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_bluespot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Conjurer</span><br>  Posts: 295<br> <font color=#333333>(3/5/03 3:00:30 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub102.ezboard.com/fthemagicianstowerthingstokill.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=452.topic&index=4>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> <img src="http://www.ezboard.com/images/posticons/pi_question_mark.gif" align=absmiddle>  Re: Soloing summoning mobs</span><hr size=1> Chaining pets whether you nuke or not will accumulate aggro on the mage.  I was two boxing Moktor's in UP with my Mage/Enchanter (for slow), chaining greater voc. earth on the MOB.  By the third pet the Moktor started summoning me.  It summoned me 2 or 3 times before the pet taunted aggro onto itself.  I wasn't nuking until the mob was at about 10%.<br>
<br>
BTW, I made the MOBs &quot;burn&quot; their summon when I was recasting.  I started casting my new pet, spammed the pet back off button (no pet hold).  The mob would summon the pet, then I would do the standard /pet get lost just before the cast was finished without being summoned (and interrupted). <p>--------------------------<br>
